<p>I have a <code>List&lt;Map&gt;</code> which should be of the below syntax:</p>  <pre><code>[{clientName=abcd}, {clientName=defg}] </code></pre>  <p>Previously I had <code>List&lt;Bean&gt;</code> which I want to replace with <code>List&lt;Map&gt;</code>. </p>  <p>Here is my code:</p>  <pre><code>List&lt;Map&gt; clientList=new ArrayList&lt;Map&gt;(); Map&lt;String,String&gt; clientNameMap = new HashMap&lt;String,String&gt;();      clientNameMap.put("clientName","abcd");     clientList.add(clientNameMap);      clientNameMap.put("clientName","defg");     clientList.add(clientNameMap); </code></pre>  <p>What happens with this code is, I am getting <code>[{clientName=defg}, {clientName=defg}]</code> as the output where, <code>clientName=abcd</code> is replaced by the 2nd value <code>defg</code>. How can I get the expected result which is  <code>[{clientName=abcd}, {clientName=defg}]</code>?</p>  <p>Thanks</p>